DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260429T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260429T200000
SUMMARY:Wednesday Night Walk: Petaluma Downtown & Riverfront
DESCRIPTION:"SONOMA COUNTY OUTDOORS"\nWednesday Night Walk: Petaluma Downt
 own and Riverfront\n\n* Want to walk for fitness and exercise?\n* New to w
 alking and want to build up stamina?\n* Like a slower pace than our Tuesda
 y Night Fitness Hike?\n* Would walking with a committed group of walkers h
 elp you?\n\nIf you said yes to any of these\, then the Wednesday Night Wal
 k in Petaluma is for you. We start at Aqus Cafe and take in the West Side 
 of town\, including some of Downtown\, the Waterfront and a few of the His
 toric home of old Petaluma. We walk about 3-1/2 to 4-1/2 miles depending o
 n weather conditions and the pace of the group that night.\n\nAfterward if
  you have the time\, join us at Aqus Cafe for a bite to eat and some liqui
 d refreshment before heading home. Aqus Cafe is a true gem of a gathering 
 place\, restaurant\, coffee house\, and live music venue. But it's the peo
 ple on either side of the counter that make this place so special.\n\nDETA
 ILS:\n\n* Meetup time: 6:00pm (we hike at 6:10 sharp)\n* Meetup location: 
 Aqus Cafe\n* Distance: 3.5 to 4-1/2 miles\n* Duration: 75-80 minutes\n* Pa
 ce: Easy/Moderate (about 2.5-3 mph or 20-24 minute miles)\n* Difficulty: E
 asy (if you've walked 3-4 miles recently)\n* Hills: Mostly flat with a few
  small and easy to climb hills\n* Optional After-Hike Gathering at Aqus Ca
 fe\n\nWHAT TO BRING:\n\n* A good pair of walking shoes\n* Water (you'll be
  glad you did)\n* A fun attitude!\n\nSO HOW FAST ARE WE WALKING?\nThe Wedn
 esday Night Walk is about 2.5 - 3 mph (20-24 minute miles)\nThe Tuesday Ni
 ght Fitness Hike is about 3.5-4 mph (15-17 minute miles)\n\nHOW DO YOU PAR
 TICIPATE?\nSign up with Meetup and RSVP Today! This also gets you on our e
 mail list to make you aware of upcoming events\, hikes and walks. You will
  not be spammed. If you are\, let me know. Spamming will not be tolerated.
 \n\nWHY DO YOU NEED TO RSVP?\nIt's important to RSVP for these walks. When
  all the people have arrived for a walk that have RSVP'd\, we leave... it 
 might mean we leave early. If you didn't RSVP we are not going to wait for
  you. Plus\, it's just a nice courtesy to the organizer and other particip
 ants. Please take the time to RSVP.\n\nQUESTIONS?\nEmail me with any quest
 ions by using the "Contact Us" link on the left hand side bar of this meet
 up group page.\n\nHope to see you on a walk or hike soon!\n\nGary\nSCO Org
 anizer
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-outdoors/events/3126132
 01/
