BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Sonoma County Outdoors
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-outdoors/
UID:event_vnmwktyjchbhb@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260404T025023Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260505T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260505T200000
SUMMARY:Tuesday Night Fitness Hike: 5+ Fast Miles\, Downtown Petaluma and 
 Western Hills
DESCRIPTION:"SONOMA COUNTY OUTDOORS"\nWARNING: THE TUESDAY NIGHT FITNESS H
 IKE IS AN AEROBIC\, FAST-PACED URBAN HIKE! WE TARGET A PACE OF 16-MINUTES 
 PER MILE WITH ONLY BRIEF STOPS (TO REGROUP AS NEEDED). OUR SUMMER ROUTE IN
 CLUDES THE HILLS IN HELEN PUTNAM PARK (740 FT. ELEVATION GAIN)\, AND OUR W
 INTER ROUTE EXPLORES THE WATER TANKS (690 FT. ELEVATION GAIN). IF YOU FIND
  YOU ARE HAVING DIFFICULTY KEEPING UP WITH THE LEADERS IN THIS GROUP\, PLE
 ASE USE THE OPT-OUT POINT AT THE FIRST MILE OF THE HIKE! ANOTHER OPTION IS
  OUR WEDNESDAY NIGHT WALK FOR A MORE MODERATE PACE. THANK YOU FOR HELPING 
 ME KEEP THIS HIKE AN AEROBIC WORKOUT!\n\nNOTE:\nThe Tuesday Night Fitness 
 Hike is posted on the SCO Calendar every week. Steve Tubbs is shown as the
  host each week but he might\, or might not\, show up to the event. This i
 s\, more often than not\, a small group of regular\, fit walkers who show 
 up on time every Tuesday night to enjoy this rigorous walk. We leave promp
 tly at 6:10 pm from the Kentucky Street entrance to the LanMart Building. 
 So\, if you don't see Steve on the Tuesday night you are there\, you might
  see him on the next one.\n\nTuesday Night Fitness Hike\, 5+ miles fast pa
 ced urban hike:\n\nThis Fitness Hike includes multiple steep uphill portio
 ns in Helen Putnam Park (during Daylight Savings Time)\, and at the Petalu
 ma Water Tanks (after Daylight Savings Time ends).\n\nTuesday Night Fitnes
 s Hike:\n\n* Warning! This is a FAST hike... a real workout!\n* 5+ miles\n
 * Meetup time 6:00 pm (We hike at 6:10 sharp)\n* Difficulty is STRENUOUS!\
 n* 90 minutes\n\nThis is a fast\, evening Fitness Hike that starts downtow
 n outside (on the sidewalk) of the LanMart Building (Brixx Restaurant\, He
 ebe Jeebe) on Kentucky Street. We head west to Helen Putnam Park (or the P
 etaluma Water Tanks when DST ends) for some beautiful vistas before return
 ing to our starting point on Kentucky Street. This hike is generally the s
 ame route and is focused primarily on fitness.\n\nWHAT TO BRING:\n\n* A go
 od pair of walking/hiking shoes\n* Water (you'll be glad you did)\n* A fun
  attitude!\n\nWHAT ABOUT THE DARKNESS?\nBring a SMALL flashlight. The side
 walks can be treacherous in west Petaluma\, and you'll want to see those c
 rags\, cracks and upheavals in the concrete. Reflective clothing is also r
 ecommended so that vehicles can see you!\n\nSO HOW FAST ARE WE WALKING?\nT
 he Wednesday Night Walk is about 2.5 mph (22 - 23 minute miles)\nThe Tuesd
 ay Night Fitness Hike nearly 3.5 - 4.0 mph (we target a 16 minute mile\, w
 ith multiple hills!)\n\nHOW DO YOU PARTICIPATE?\nSign up with Meetup and R
 SVP Today! This also gets you on our email list to make you aware of upcom
 ing events\, hikes and walks.\n\nWHY DO YOU NEED TO RSVP?\n\nPlease take t
 he time to RSVP YES when you plan on attending an event. It is equally imp
 ortant to keep your RSVP up to date. If you've RSVP'd YES for an event\, w
 e are going to wait for you until the departure time. We leave promptly at
  6:10 PM\, so if you arrive late you can join us along the route. We typic
 ally hike the same route for each hike\, and our focus is on aerobic exerc
 ise.\n\nQUESTIONS?\nEmail me with any questions by using the "Contact Us" 
 link on the left hand side bar of this meetup group page.\n\nHope to see y
 ou on a walk or hike soon!\n\nSCO Organizers
